</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'><a
href=3D"http://thinkprogress.org/2009/12/07/koch-swiftboat-science/">http:/=
/thinkprogress.org/2009/12/07/koch-swiftboat-science/</a></span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:24.0pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>Right-wing
billionaire&nbsp;<a
href=3D"http://www.boston.com/bostonglobe/editorial_opinion/oped/articles/2=
009/12/06/in_glitzy_shadows_a_health_reform_foe_lurks/">David
Koch</a>, who along with his brother Charles owns the oil and gas empire Ko=
ch
Industries, constantly presents himself as a champion of science. Next year=
, a
wing of the Smithsonian will be named after him because of his generous
donations. Indeed, in accepting Koch&#8217;s donations, the Smithsonian Hum=
an Origins
Program director Rick Potts attempted to<a
href=3D"http://www.kansas.com/news/breaking/story/1012506.html">whitewash K=
och&#8217;s
philanthropist history</a>:</span><span style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-=
serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>POTTS:&nbsp;<b>What
we find in David Koch is a person who&#8217;s committed to doing things for=
 the
American public that has no relationship to politics</b></span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>Koch
apparently relishes this perception that his money buys. In an interview
earlier this year, Koch pretended that he opposes organizations which&nbsp;=
<a
href=3D"http://www.suzanmazur.com/?p=3D3">politicize and distort science</a=
>:</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>Q:
What role do you think politics should play in educating the public about
evolution?</span><span style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:=
p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>KOCH:
That&#8217;s an interesting question.<b>&nbsp;I think politicians should re=
ally stay
out of it and allow scientists to present the facts and discoveries. I hate=
 to
see it politicized</b>.</span><span style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-seri=
f"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>In
an op-ed in the&nbsp;<a
href=3D"http://www.boston.com/bostonglobe/editorial_opinion/oped/articles/2=
009/12/06/in_glitzy_shadows_a_health_reform_foe_lurks/">Boston
Globe</a>&nbsp;yesterday, I observed that Koch has manufactured a positive
image for himself by giving to laudable causes, while at the same time, qui=
etly
&#8220;<a
href=3D"http://www.boston.com/bostonglobe/editorial_opinion/oped/articles/2=
009/12/06/in_glitzy_shadows_a_health_reform_foe_lurks/">funneling
tens of millions of dollars</a>&nbsp;to more subterranean efforts that refl=
ect
his conservative politics.&#8221; Despite his funding of the Smithsonian, K=
och has
done more to politicize and and undermine the public&#8217;s understanding =
of science
than any other single person. Koch has funded the leading groups dedicated =
to
spreading skepticism of climate change:</span><span style=3D'font-family:"A=
rial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&#8211;
Koch&#8217;s Americans for Prosperity, the right-wing tea party group which
Koch&nbsp;<a
href=3D"http://www.boston.com/bostonglobe/editorial_opinion/oped/articles/2=
009/12/06/in_glitzy_shadows_a_health_reform_foe_lurks/">founded
in 1984</a>&nbsp;and continues to finance, has just announced that it will =
send
a team of political operatives to Copenhagen for the United Nations Climate
Change Conference.&nbsp;<b>AFP intends to hold a press conference to attack=
 any
climate change solution the President promises as a mistake that will &#822=
0;kill
jobs here&#8221; and &#8220;</b><a
href=3D"http://americansforprosperity.org/120209-hot-air-tour-live-copenhag=
en"><b>infringe
on our personal and national freedoms</b></a><b>.&#8221;</b></span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&#8211;
Koch has funded the Competitive Enterprise Institute, which has been the<b>=
&nbsp;most
aggressive conservative front group heralding hacked e-mails</b><a
href=3D"http://mediamatters.org/research/200912040022"><b>as proof that cli=
mate
change</b></a><b>&nbsp;does not exist.</b></span><span style=3D'font-family=
:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&#8211;
Koch funds the &#8220;<a href=3D"http://www.hotairtour.org/index.php?conten=
t=3Dmedia">Hot
Air Tour</a>,&#8221; a campaign led by&nbsp;<a
href=3D"http://wonkroom.thinkprogress.org/2009/05/29/afp-timphillips-astrot=
urf/">lobbyists</a>&nbsp;stopping
in cities across the country to&nbsp;<b>call into question the science
underpinning climate change. The tour also features an actual hot air ballo=
on
to illustrate their beleif that climate change science is just &#8220;hot a=
ir.&#8221;</b></span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>&nbsp;</span><span
style=3D'font-family:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

<div>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial","s=
ans-serif"'>The
National Academy of Sciences, the US Global Change Research Program, and th=
e
Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change have all come to the&nbsp;<a
href=3D"http://www.boston.com/bostonglobe/editorial_opinion/editorials/arti=
cles/2009/12/07/dont_suppress_debate_win_it/">same
conclusion</a>: &#8220;that carbon dioxide emissions from fossil fuel use a=
nd the
loss of carbon-sink capacity in heavily timbered forests are increasing
temperatures and making oceans more acidic.&#8221; David Koch&#8217;s Koch =
Industries
derives much of its profit from its oil refineries, one of the major emitte=
rs
of carbon dioxide, and from its George-Pacific timber subsidiary, one of th=
e
largest contributors to the loss of carbon-sink capacity. So while it&#8217=
;s clear
Koch&#8217;s bottom line is in conflict with the addressing the world&#8217=
;s climate
crisis, it should also be clear that he is no champion of science &#8212; n=
o matter
how many halls he buys at the Smithsonian.</span><span style=3D'font-family=
:"Arial","sans-serif"'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

